                            <comment id="16821665" author="sunedge" created="Fri, 19 Apr 2019 04:57:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s very important. Please who can fix this please fix it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16821678" author="tilman" created="Fri, 19 Apr 2019 05:36:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;What do you mean? I got an image that looks like Adobe Reader. Please explain what you expected and what happened instead, i.e. attach your image and a screenshot what you expected instead.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16821687" author="sunedge" created="Fri, 19 Apr 2019 06:06:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hello &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=tilman&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;tilman&quot;&gt;tilman&lt;/a&gt;,&lt;br/&gt;
 We&apos;ve problem converting pdf to image.&lt;br/&gt;
 I attached files.&lt;br/&gt;
 Can you help me, Please&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16821774" author="tilman" created="Fri, 19 Apr 2019 08:33:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I can reproduce the problem with your new PDF.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These are type 3 fonts with a text rendering mode of 3 (= invisible). It turns out PDFBox ignores that flag for type 3 fonts, so it paints these &quot;glyphs&quot;. The type 3 charprocs show black rectangles (no color is set). This is easy to fix and now I&apos;ll do some regression tests.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
